The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, April 23, 2004 				 Nalco probe stayed 
																								Mumbai, April 22 (PTI): Bombay High Court today stayed the departmental probe by National Aluminium Corporation into allegations of molestation of a female employee by its chief, C. Venkataramana.																								The stay was granted by Justices Ajit Shah and Abhay Oka on a complaint by the victim that the probe committee was biased against her and that she was asked to demonstrate the alleged act of molestation during the inquiry. The court has adjourned the matter to April 28.																								The court also gone through the questions posed by the probe committee to the victim and the answers given by her. The judges observed that they were prima facie satisfied that the probe was not being conducted properly.																								The court had earlier, on a petition filed by the victim, ordered Nalco to probe the allegations of molestation in keeping with the Supreme Courts guidelines with regard to sexual harassment at workplaces.
